 close reading uncovers the real scope of Lacan's criticism regarding the moralizing ethics of our time, and is one of the rare books that gives the reader full access to the letter of the Lacanian text.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aPsychoanalysisxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aPsychoanalysisxPhilosophy. 4aLiterature : Literary Theory. 4aPhilosophy : Ethics. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPsychology : Psychoanalysis. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Movements / Psychoanalysis.2bisacsh1 aJöttkandt, Sigi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143842634140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438426341423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438426341/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles